profile_positions.description:
Duo (combination) role with Key Account Manager Business Travel.

As Manager Strategic Partnerships at Booking.com I managed key affiliate partners in the Benelux & Nordic region. 
Working specifically in the mobile vertical I supported the Partnerships team in this space across the region with a focus on new and existing partnerships. 

Responsibilities: 
- Provide support to Booking.com BV in maintaining and building successful business partnerships with Booking.com BV’s strategic partners and manage the aspects of partner interactions;
- Monitor the success of each account and manage client relationships by advising on Booking.com BV’s services;
- Promote Booking.com BV’s brand name and its online reservation services to the potential business partners;
- Support Booking.com BV in research, identification and segmentation of business opportunities regarding strategic partners (affiliate websites/mobile platforms) to increase the number of potential visitors and traffic on the Booking.com website;
- Highlight behaviors and key trends in the designated market;
- Establish an understanding of the business objectives of these partners and match these with the range of services of Booking.com BV to maximize business opportunities;
- Manage all processes leading up to provide support to Booking.com BV in finalizing such partnerships (i.e. leads, prospecting, establishing first contact, meetings, contract, integration and follow up);
- Build and maintain a professional network within the travel web industry;
- Proactively support the business and report to Area Manager strategic Partnerships;
- Monitor, research and report findings on market developments in the travel industry.

I enjoyed optimizing Global hotel programs by content integration on various travel & expense systems with C-level decision makers of companies with 5000+ employees HQ based in the Benelux & Nordics.

In order to align on a full service model I collaborated with global travel suppliers (TMC's) and SaaS solutions (OBE's) on advising corporate customers on savings and extra benefits to mainly ensure duty or care and travel policy compliance. My main tasks:

- New business development and key accounting; 
- Forecasting; 
- First point of contact for Corporate Enterprise Clients;
- Support Travel-managers / Procurement Managers on long-term goals and new initiatives; 
- Monitor research and report findings on market developments in the travel industry;
- Set up internal growth strategy plan; 
- Answering RFP's (tender-management) submitted by corporate enterprise clients; 
- Support with implementing a Corporate Travel Program within a company; 
- Aggregating and analyzing feedback to support product initiatives; 
- Proactively identify opportunities to improve customer experience and operational efficiency;
- Work with internal support department and corporate enterprise client on long-term goals and new initiatives to support Booking.com BV in maximizing growth and meeting customer needs;
- Liaise with corporate enterprise clients and internal support departments to solve ongoing issues.

As an Account Manager I am responsible for hotel account management initially. I support Booking.com BV’s acquisition of new hotels in a specific area in The Netherlands. I create quantity and quality reports on results and performance for information support to Booking.com. 
Responsible for maximising the performance of our partners. Through big data analyses and frequent partner contact I identify and evaluate market trends on city level & individual accommodation performance.

Main Responsibilities:
-  Visit the important hotels in The Netherlands (South);
-  Acquisition; 
-  Support Booking.com BV’s-strategy for hotel availability and supply within The Netherlands;
-  Promote the Booking.com BV brand name and its online reservation services to hotels;
-  Responsible for area coverage;
-  Inform hotels and advise on allotment, availability and supply;
-  Rate checks and competitor checks;
-  Liaison person for hotels to contact when they have questions;
-  Providing hotels with information and advice by email, including follow-ups;
-  Follow up on cancellations and evaluations;
-  Accompany and train hotels on how to use Booking.com’s extranet and rates & availability system;
-  Support hotels with regards to Booking.com’s system;
-  Organize and coordinate Tourist Trade Fair visits to liaise with hotels;
-  Check statistics in the control room and follow up;

- Pro-active communication with partners by telephone and by internal messaging to assist with the development of Booking.com's business;
-Responsible for a portfolio of partners - first point of contact, answering questions and following up when needed;
-Responsible for maintaining a stable relationship with the accommodation partners (i.e. frequent performance calls and contact to ensure they offer Booking.coms customers the best availability and competitive pricing);
-Identify opportunities for partners that help improve Booking.coms business by using its internal segmentation to prioritize;
-Help identifying new potential partner leads and pass these leads on for further follow up;
-Responsible for taking Customer Service escalations which relate to their managed portfolio and solving these in the most efficient manner for the business, partner and customer;
-Support on events, such as workshops and webinars, for partners. Participation in partner events for my managed portfolio.
